observations.recommendation:
Submit the bank reconciliation statements for CY 2023 for all cash in bank accounts and ensure that the reports will be regularly submitted then;

Submit also the supporting documents of the BRS such as Bank Statements and Subsidiary Ledger; and

Analyze the cash variance in bank accounts, prepare and submit adjusting entries, and reconcile with Municipal Treasurer’s records regularly.

The Inventory Committee to conduct annual physical inventory to include all the PPEs of the LGU and prepare properly and completely the corresponding RPCPPE;

The General Services Office to maintain Property Cards for all PPE Accounts;

The Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards for each category of assets and Real Property Ledger Cards for land to back up the general ledger for PPE; and

The Accounting and GSO to reconcile their records to obtain the accurate value of PPE, prepare the required supporting documents and draw the adjusting journal entries for the inventory items remaining in the books but are already non-existent due to wear and tear, thereby fairly present the balance of the property accounts in the financial statements.

Establish specific guidelines setting the rules and regulations on the grant of financial assistance and adequate measures in implementing and granting financial assistance to individuals/recipients;

Direct the MSWD Coordinator to make and submit a case study/assessment before forwarding the names to the Mayor’s Office; and

Require the recipients through the Municipal Accountant to submit the Certificate of Indigency, ID of the claimant and any proof to validate the need of cash assistance, within 15 days from the receipt hereof, otherwise we will be constrained to issue a Notice of Suspension pursuant to COA Circular 2009-006 dated Sept. 15,2009 “Prescribing the use of the Rules and Regulations on Settlement of Accounts”.

Direct the BAC to submit the required supporting documents to substantiate their claims on honoraria;

Require the BAC Chairman, BAC Members and BAC Secretariat to refund the overpayment of honoraria if not substantiated; and

Observe strict compliance with implementing rules and regulations of procurement law on the qualifications of Bids and Awards Committee (BAC), BAC Secretariat and Technical Working Group (TWG) and the prescribed rates per DBM Budget Circular No. 2007-5A.

Require all Department Heads or implementing units to prepare their respective Project Procurement Management Plans (PPMPs) for their different programs, activities and projects (PAPs) in the format prescribed by the Government Procurement Policy Board (GPPB) and linkage to the approved annual budget;

Direct the BAC Secretariat to consolidate the PPMPs into Annual Procurement Plan (APP) in the format prescribed by GPPB Circular 08-2015 and to submit the report independent of the annual budget of the Municipality; and

Require all the BAC Chairman, BAC members and BAC Secretariat to attend relevant trainings and seminars on procurement planning and budgeting.

Require the Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of RA 9184 in the conduct of public bidding and awarding of the contracts to prevent possible pre-arranged bidding and ensure genuine competition;

Post all results of bidding and related information in the PhilGEPS website;

Ensure that bidders submit complete eligibility requirements and all documentary requirements before signing the contract; and

Instruct the BAC to submit the lacking contract agreements of three infrastructure projects and ensure that prospective contracts are submitted within the prescribed period.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that withholding taxes are deducted from payments of honoraria to avoid penalties;

Increase manpower or assign employees in the Municipal Accountant’s Office, in case of heavy workloads, to function as a pre-audit and to ensure that taxes are correctly withheld; and

Refund the overpayment and remit it to the BIR.

Transmit immediately all contracts still pending for submission together with the perfected contracts for the current year and prior years with all the documents forming part thereof for COA’s review and to submit prospective contracts within five (5) days after the perfection of the contract;

Submit request of technical inspection of completed project along with the necessary documents needed pursuant to Annex C of COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009; and

Revisit the internal control policies over LGU procurement operation to identify and address these recurring lapses and delay over submission of contracts.

Direct the Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the municipality and render a Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System;

Instruct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Designated Municipal General Service Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;

Instruct the Designated Municipal General Service Officer to render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map and to keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to record the municipal roads and its components based on the appraisal of the Municipal Engineer and to maintain property ledger cards for each infrastructure for proper monitoring of transactions.

Instruct the Bids and Awards Committee to ensure compliance with RA 9184, its IRR and related issuance in future procurement transactions particularly on posting of the Annual Procurement Plan in the GPPB website, providing a copy of the APP in the disbursement voucher; to provide specifications in the Purchase Request; to submit proof of invitation to observers; to stop the reference of brand name, and to submit post qualification report and BAC resolution whenever the alternative method of procurement will be adopted; 

Direct the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly follow the procedures in Section 52 of RA 9184 or Shopping as alternative mode of procurement and to attach a request for quotation and abstract of canvass as required in Section 9.2.4 of COA Circular 2012-001; and

Require the General Supply Office and BAC to consider first procurement of ordinary office supplies and equipment at PS DBM or to its depots in compliance with Section 1 of Administrative Order No. 17 in order to avail of the price that is most advantage to the government.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the –
Municipal Accountant to undertake controls and strategies in order to ensure adherence with the required time frame for the submission of monthly trial balance, quarterly financial statements and other reports;
Municipal Budget Officer to ensure submission of monthly SAAOB and to submit immediately the latest SAAOB for CY 2024 not later than March 30, 2025;
Municipal Engineer to ensure that the list of all on-going PPAs and those that are to be implemented for the year will be submitted every beginning of the year; and submit monthly monitoring report of awarded infrastructure projects, programs and activities (PPAs) within 10 days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the PPAs and that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted.

We recommended the Local Chief Executive to:
Require the Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of RA 9184 in the conduct of public bidding and awarding of the contracts to prevent possible pre-arranged bidding and ensure genuine competition;
Post all results of bidding and related information in the PhilGEPS website;
Ensure that bidders submit complete eligibility requirements and all documentary requirements before signing the contract; and
Instruct the BAC to submit the lacking contract agreements of three infrastructure projects and ensure that prospective contracts are submitted within the prescribed period.

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to discontinue or minimize the practice of granting multiple cash advances on a particular day to the Disbursing Officers but instead pay directly under the name of the payees, concerned employees and suppliers;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to record transactions that are cash advances in nature with the appropriate Advances account(s) applicable and not as outright expenses. Make the necessary adjusting entries; and

Direct the Disbursing Officers to submit liquidation reports with complete supporting documents of their cash advances as of December 31, 2023 within 15 days from receipt hereof, otherwise the transactions shall be suspended pursuant to COA Circular 2009-006 prescribing the rules and regulations on settlement of accounts.

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to:

Ensure that the annual appropriations for Extraordinary and Miscellaneous Expenses for the discretionary expenses of the local chief executive shall not exceed two percent (2%) of the actual receipts derived from basic real property tax in the next preceding calendar year and that no other amount shall be appropriated for the same purpose;


Direct the Municipal Accountant to make necessary adjustment(s) to reclassify the various expenses that were recorded in the Extraordinary and Miscellaneous Expenses account for the fair presentation of the accounts in the financial statements. Said account should be used only for the expenses described in the Revised Chart of Accounts.

Transmit immediately all contracts still pending for submission together with the perfected contracts for the current year and prior years with all the documents forming part thereof for COA’s review and to submit prospective contracts within five (5) days after the perfection of the contract;

Submit request of technical inspection of completed project along with the necessary documents needed pursuant to Annex C of COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009; and

Revisit the internal control policies over LGU procurement operation to identify and address these recurring lapses and delay over submission of contracts.

