Require the Supply Officer and RHU to coordinate and come up with a clear defined responsibility for proper inventory-taking, reporting, supervision and disposition of the transferred drugs, medicines and medical supplies from DOH, PHO and the Commission on Population and Development;

Require the Supply Officer to inform the Municipal Accountant and furnish her with the receipt of asset for her to recognize it in the books basing on the PTRs issued by the DOH;

Ensure that the receiving officer requires that PTRs are duly approved and value of items received are indicated properly otherwise coordinate with the DOH and PHO source agency for that matter; and

Require preparation of Distribution and Utilization Report for accounting, evaluation and documentation purposes.

Require the submission of lacking documentary requirements for travels by all personnel indicated in Annex H in accordance with COA Circular No. 2021-001, otherwise direct refund of travels claimed;

Adjust/reclassify erroneous entries to the appropriate account(s) for proper accounting in conformity with Volume III of the GAM for LGUs;

Stop payment of gasoline and fuel cost as transportation expense and cost of actual meals and lodging expenses for travel claims by employees. Adhere strictly to EO No. 77 for computation of allowable travel claims; and

Require revision of IT’s by those who claimed for actual costs of gasoline and actual meals and recompute for allowable traveling expense using the current rate to establish if traveling expenses claimed were not excessive, otherwise, direct refund of the excess.

Facilitate the adoption of automation of payroll or payroll-thru-bank system for the payment of salaries and wages of the permanent employees and JO personnel to avoid security risks involving payrolls and to promote operational efficiency;

The HRMO to require the employees without ATM cards to submit their application forms to the LBP as a requirement for subsequent issuance of ATM cards to them and coordinate with the LBP officials and employees for the processing of the same; and

See to it that Cash Advances granted shall not exceed the maximum cash accountability authorized under her approved fidelity bond or else apply for an increased fidelity bond.

The Municipal Budget/AAO designate to provide the Municipal Accountant with monthly billing statements and ERF and a detailed report on the unremitted GSIS contributions, duly supported with a reconciliation of past billing statements and remittances;

The Municipal Accountant to attached the monthly billing statements and ERF in the monthly remittances; and

The AAO (i) to remit regularly the GSIS contributions to prevent accumulation of the same and to avoid undue penalties, surcharges and interests imposed by the GSIS and (ii) to observe prompt submission of ARA to GSIS whenever there are changes in members’ data to ensure timely updating of the GSIS database and to prevent inaccuracies in the billing statements.

Prepare and submit Journal Entry Vouchers drawn for all non-cash transactions or adjustments in order to facilitate verification in determining the correctness of the amount recorded;

Use proper and correct account names and account codes in accordance with PPSAS;

Strictly comply on the prescribed time to submit journal vouchers to COA; and

Maintain subsidiary ledger and general ledger for all accounts.

