Require the GAD Focal Person and MPDC to conduct gender mainstreaming to identify the appropriate activities responsive to the needs of the LGU constituents; 

Establish and maintain a GAD Database in implementing the Magna Carta for Women which helps in formulating GAD-related activities based on information gathered; and 

Prepare and submit Annual GAD Accomplishment Report including all its supporting documents as prescribed under DILG-NEDA Joint Circular No. 2013-01.

Create inventory committee and to prepare a timetable for the conduct of Physical Inventory for a cohesive planning; Strictly comply with the required physical count of all properties at least once a year and to submit a copy of the Inventory Report to the Audit Team not later than January 31 and every year;

Consider appointing/designating other employee as GSO and/ or augment the work force or staff in the GSO specifically during the conduct of inventory taking;

Make representation with the previous administration to turn-over the property not yet in the custody of the Municipality, otherwise request for a write-off of these property and institute judicial proceedings for violation of ordinances in the recovery of property; and

Require the Municipal Accountant and Designate-GSO to maintain Property Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively, and shall henceforth conduct periodic reconciliation of the balances of both records.

Stop the practice of using cash advance to pay for the Municipality’s operating expenses particularly for GAD and LCPC activities; 

Ensure that disbursements should be issued with check directly to the name of the payees, concerned employees, and suppliers; and 

Submit all Report of Disbursements for CY 2019.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the November and December 2019 disbursement vouchers not later March 31, 2020 and to make necessary strategies in order to comply with the submission of accounts within the reporting deadlines;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to approve and process only those disbursement vouchers supported with complete and valid documentations and approvals; and

Augment the working force under the Accounting Office with great consideration on the competency and qualification.

Ensure that programs, projects and activities are responsive to the needs of the children and pursuant to those identified in the Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC); and

Direct the Council to prepare the following reports:

Council's Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the local development plan;
Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC); 
Local Investment Plan for Children (LIPC);
Local State of Children's Report.

Prioritize the GSIS contribution over and above the payment of any and all obligations except salaries and wages of its employees in the LGU in conformity with Section 6 of Republic Act No. 8291 otherwise known as the GSIS Act of 1997;

Remit regularly the GSIS contributions to prevent accumulation of the same to avoid undue penalties, surcharges and interests imposed by the GSIS; 

Make a further representation with the GSIS to secure the MOA in order to settle the past due balances with the agency; and

Allocate a budget in the succeeding year for the prior years’ unremitted contributions.

